		},
		{
			"id": "T1mKftlv",
			"type": "text",
			"x": 1896.1075797202752,
			"y": 1224.2272397320246,
			"width": 443.94183349609375,
			"height": 945.0000000000001,
			"angle": 0,
			"strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
			"backgroundColor": "#fff9db",
			"fillStyle": "solid",
			"strokeWidth": 0.5,
			"strokeStyle": "solid",
			"roughness": 1,
			"opacity": 100,
			"groupIds": [],
			"frameId": null,
			"index": "avh",
			"roundness": null,
			"seed": 2124587819,
			"version": 482,
			"versionNonce": 762889952,
			"isDeleted": false,
			"boundElements": [],
			"updated": 1758744681398,
			"link": null,
			"locked": false,
			"text": "Normal users do not interact\ndirectly with history tables.\n\nHistory tables are append-only.\nEvery past state of every collection\nitem is stored in its history table.\n\n1 collection item ⬅➡ many rows. \n\"Item\" means \"has same collection\nitem id\". There is a separate,\nunique PK, the history id\n(xxx_hx_id), for each row in the\nhistory table.\n\nThe history table and the main\ntable are maintained such that the\nlatest history record for each\n(undeleted) item is the same as the\nmain record for it; deleted items\nare of course not present in\nprimary table.\n\nHistory tables contain additional \ninformation specifically related to \nhistory-tracking.",
			"rawText": "Normal users do not interact directly with history tables.\n\nHistory tables are append-only. Every past state of every collection item is stored in its history table.\n\n1 collection item ⬅➡ many rows. \n\"Item\" means \"has same collection item id\". There is a separate, unique PK, the history id (xxx_hx_id), for each row in the history table.\n\nThe history table and the main table are maintained such that the latest history record for each (undeleted) item is the same as the main record for it; deleted items are of course not present in primary table.\n\nHistory tables contain additional \ninformation specifically related to \nhistory-tracking.",
			"fontSize": 28,
			"fontFamily": 6,
			"textAlign": "left",
			"verticalAlign": "middle",
			"containerId": "P1OrraxFxBntBybZIMhag",
			"originalText": "Normal users do not interact directly with history tables.\n\nHistory tables are append-only. Every past state of every collection item is stored in its history table.\n\n1 collection item ⬅➡ many rows. \n\"Item\" means \"has same collection item id\". There is a separate, unique PK, the history id (xxx_hx_id), for each row in the history table.\n\nThe history table and the main table are maintained such that the latest history record for each (undeleted) item is the same as the main record for it; deleted items are of course not present in primary table.\n\nHistory tables contain additional \ninformation specifically related to \nhistory-tracking.",
			"autoResize": true,
			"lineHeight": 1.35
		}
	],
